CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 10, 1945, pg. 14, reads: "The Pacific was Never Like This - Friends of Corp. Joseph Mackell, who has been on duty in the South Pacific for the past three years, threw a party for him at the home of his parents, Mr. and Mrs. Benjamin Mackell, 2327 Centre Avenue, Monday night. Mackell is pictured here with his arms around his parents. They have another son, Thomas, who is at present on duty in England. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Guests at party for Corp. Joseph Mackell standing near left with arms around parents Mrs. Mackell and Benjamin Mackell in their home, 2327 Centre Avenue, Hill District
